\description{
The rack layer is the storage abstraction behind blockr session
persistence: it turns a save into a stored, versioned record and a load back
into board state. The shipped backend dispatches on \pkg{pins} boards (see
\code{\link[=user_pins_board]{user_pins_board()}}), but the contract is storage-agnostic -- a database or
document store is supported by implementing the generics documented here and
carrying the \code{rack_backend} class, which is what wiring a non-pins backend
into the \code{session_mgmt_backend} \code{\link[blockr.core:blockr_option]{blockr.core::blockr_option()}} requires. The
high-level \code{\link[=rack_create]{rack_create()}},
\code{\link[=rack_append]{rack_append()}} and \code{\link[=rack_load]{rack_load()}} entry points that application code calls
are built on these generics.
}
\details{
Two kinds of object flow through the contract. A \emph{backend} is the board or
store itself, the dispatch target for \code{as_rack_id()}, \code{rack_capabilities()},
\code{rack_list()}, \code{rack_upload()} and \code{rack_find_users()}. A \code{rack_id} is a
handle to one stored record, the dispatch target for the remaining generics.
\code{\link[=as_rack_id]{as_rack_id()}} coerces a raw identifier -- a component list or a
\code{rack_record} listing row -- into the backend's own \code{rack_id} subclass (via
\code{new_rack_id(..., class = )}) from the components (\code{id}, \code{version}, \code{user})
carried in a session URL, and returns an existing \code{rack_id} unchanged.
\code{rack_list()} returns \code{\link[=new_rack_record]{new_rack_record()}} summaries, the listing rows the
workflow menu renders.
}
\section{Capabilities}{

\code{rack_capabilities()} is the feature switch: it returns a named list of
logical flags declaring which optional features the backend supports, and
the management UI gates the matching generics on it.
\itemize{
\item \code{versioning}: a version history is kept per record: \code{rack_info()} lists it
and \code{rack_download()} / \code{rack_delete()} accept a version.
\item \code{tags}: \code{rack_tags()} and \code{rack_set_tags()} are implemented.
\item \code{metadata}: a display name (\code{rack_name()}, \code{rack_rename()}) and a content
hash (\code{rack_content_hash()}) are stored alongside the payload.
\item \code{sharing}: \code{rack_share()}, \code{rack_unshare()} and \code{rack_shares()} are
implemented.
\item \code{visibility}: \code{rack_acl()} and \code{rack_set_acl()} are implemented.
\item \code{user_discovery}: \code{rack_find_users()} is implemented.
}

A minimal backend implements only the core create / load / list set --
\code{as_rack_id()}, \code{rack_upload()}, \code{rack_download()}, \code{rack_exists()},
\code{rack_list()}, \code{rack_info()} and \code{rack_name()} -- and returns \code{FALSE} for
every optional capability; the generics behind a \code{FALSE} flag are then never
reached and need no method.
}

